      "source": [
        "# Chemistry Experiment Data Analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "## Aim\n",
        "To analyze experimental data and plot graph of concentration against time."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ngJ9IMLJxwMy"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Experimental Data\n",
        "data = {\n",
        "    \"Time (min)\": [0, 5, 10, 15, 20, 25],\n",
        "    \"Concentration (mol/L)\": [1.0, 0.82, 0.67, 0.55, 0.45, 0.37]\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(df)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.plot(df[\"Time (min)\"], df[\"Concentration (mol/L)\"])\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Time (min)\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Concentration (mol/L)\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Concentration vs Time\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
